   THE STORY OF MANDELA
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   President Pieter W. Botha offers to free Mandela if he renounces violence; Mandela refuses until the government takes steps to dismantle apartheid and grants full political rights to blacks. Mandela joins the African National Congress at age 26, later becoming president of the group's Youth League.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   One week later, Mandela is allowed to make his first officially sanctioned public statement since his conviction.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   In December, Mandela is arrested and charged under Suppression of Communism Act.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   From behind bars, Nelson Mandela has dominated the fight for black rights in South Africa .
